## Finding: Config Drift Detection Between Environments is Uncovered

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: The deployment_patterns skill covers configuration validation at startup (Zod schema), and the env_validation skill (Phase 5.5) covers fail-fast startup env checks. But there is no Phase 5 skill addressing: (1) detecting configuration drift between staging and production over time (e.g. a secret added to staging but not production causes a silent difference); (2) infrastructure drift between Terraform-managed state and actual cloud state; (3) container image version drift (production running v1.2.3 but Terraform/k8s manifest says v1.2.5); (4) scheduled drift detection as a continuous CI check. Configuration drift is a leading cause of "works in staging, fails in production" incidents.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill `config_drift_detection`. Triggers: "config drift", "environment parity", "drift detection". Scope: Provides scheduled GitHub Actions workflow that compares environment configurations (env var presence, not values); runs `terraform plan` in CI to detect infrastructure drift; diffs container image digests between environments; generates drift report and alerts on deviation. Covers Doppler/Infisical diff APIs for secret inventory comparison.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5.5 env_validation catches missing vars at startup but not drift accumulated over time. Phase 7 (Maintenance) has no upstream pattern for drift monitoring from Phase 5.

