## Finding: Changelog Generation and Release Notes Automation is Missing

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: The oss_publishing skill covers semantic-release for open source projects (automated CHANGELOG.md from conventional commits). The game_publishing skill has a manual Patch Notes Template. But for standard SaaS/web applications in Phase 5, there is no skill covering: (1) automated changelog generation from conventional commits for non-OSS projects; (2) release notes generation that feeds downstream platforms (GitHub Releases, deployment notifications in Slack, in-app "What's New" banners); (3) version bumping automation tied to the deployment pipeline; (4) a release notes format that bridges technical commit messages and user-facing language. The ci_cd_pipeline skill shows no changelog/release step in any workflow.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill `release_automation` (or expand ci_cd_pipeline). Triggers: "generate release notes", "automate changelog", "version bump", "release management". Scope: Integrates conventional commits with automated changelog generation for both OSS and private projects; creates GitHub Releases with release notes on each deploy-to-main; optionally posts deployment notification to Slack/Discord; supports both automated and human-curated release notes. Covers bumping version files as part of the deployment pipeline.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5.5 (Alpha) and Phase 5.75 (Beta) have no mechanism to receive structured "what changed" information from Phase 5 deployments. Phase 6 (Handoff) documentation has no upstream artifact of versioned changes.

