## Finding: Smoke Test Suite is Not a First-Class Phase 5 Artifact

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: The deployment_patterns skill mentions "smoke tests" in its Pipeline Stages section: "deploy staging → smoke tests → deploy production." The mlops skill runs "integration tests" and "shadow mode comparison" after staging deploy. But there is no dedicated skill defining what a smoke test suite is, how to build one, and how to integrate it as a mandatory post-deployment gate. The ci_cd_pipeline deploy workflow goes: build → deploy to Railway/Vercel → done. There is no "verify the deployment actually works" step. A deployment can succeed (exit code 0 from the CLI) while the application is 500-ing all requests.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill `smoke_test_suite` in Phase 5. Triggers: "smoke tests", "deployment verification", "post-deploy checks", "verify deployment". Scope: Defines a lightweight, fast (< 2 minute) smoke test suite that runs immediately after every deployment; covers: HTTP status checks on critical endpoints, auth flow verification (can a user log in?), database connectivity probe, API contract spot-checks; integrates as a GitHub Actions job that runs after deploy and rolls back automatically on failure; provides both CLI-runnable and CI-runnable formats.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5.5 health_checks covers liveness/readiness but not behavioral correctness. Phase 4 e2e_testing covers full user journeys but is too slow (minutes to hours) to run as a post-deploy gate. The gap between "deployment succeeded" and "application works" is unaddressed.

