## Finding: ci_cd_pipeline Migration Order Bug — Skill Contains Dangerous Anti-Pattern

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: The ci_cd_pipeline skill's deploy-backend.yml workflow runs `npx prisma migrate deploy` BEFORE `railway up`. Per the db_migrations skill's own "Deployment Order Matters" section, this is explicitly labeled UNSAFE: "Migrate first, then deploy code → Running code doesn't know about new schema — ERRORS." This internal contradiction between two skills in the same phase (ci_cd_pipeline and db_migrations) means following one skill's instructions correctly will violate the other's safety guidance. The ci_cd_pipeline skill also lacks any mention of the expand-and-contract pattern from db_migrations, which means users following only ci_cd_pipeline get the dangerous pattern. This is the most critical internal inconsistency found.
### Proposed Resolution: Update ci_cd_pipeline's deploy-backend.yml to use a staged deploy: (1) deploy new code that is backward-compatible with old schema, (2) run migrations, (3) optionally run a health check to confirm. Add an explicit cross-reference to db_migrations skill for the rationale. Consider adding a "migration safety check" step that reads the generated SQL and fails the pipeline if DROP or destructive ALTER statements are present without a manual approval gate.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 4 integration_testing tests migrations in isolation but does not test the deployment ORDER. Any user relying solely on ci_cd_pipeline will ship with a race condition between code and schema on every migration-bearing deploy.

