## Finding: legal_compliance Skill Has No Technical Audit Trail for Consent

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: The legal_compliance skill provides a cookie consent banner implementation and GDPR/CCPA checklists. However, it does not cover: (1) server-side consent logging — storing a record of when a user gave/withdrew consent, which version of the privacy policy they agreed to, and what they agreed to (required for GDPR accountability principle, Article 5(2)); (2) versioned policy agreement tracking in the database (the skill shows a `version: string` field on the document object but no database model for storing user agreement to each version); (3) re-consent flows when the privacy policy changes materially; (4) data subject request (DSR) fulfillment workflow — the GDPR checklist says "Right to access", "Right to erasure" etc. as checkboxes but provides no implementation; (5) automated data retention enforcement (deletion after retention period expires). The cookie consent code stores consent only in localStorage, which is not a server-side audit trail.
### Proposed Resolution: Add to legal_compliance: (1) server-side consent logging model and API endpoint; (2) DSR fulfillment workflow patterns; (3) automated data retention cron job pattern; (4) re-consent modal trigger when policy version changes. This is a GDPR compliance obligation, not a nice-to-have.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 4 security_audit covers authentication and authorization but not privacy regulation compliance. Phase 5.5 has no skill for ongoing privacy compliance monitoring.

