## Finding: mlops Skill Lacks Feature Store and Training Data Versioning

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: LOW
### Evidence: The mlops skill covers model serving, monitoring, and CI/CD for ML. However, for production ML systems, the data layer is equally critical: (1) no coverage of feature stores (Feast, Tecton, Hopsworks) for consistent feature computation between training and serving; (2) no coverage of training data versioning (DVC, LakeFS); (3) the data validation step in the CI/CD example (`validate_data.py`) has no skill-level guidance on what to validate or how; (4) no coverage of data lineage — being able to trace which data trained which model version. These are medium-maturity concerns and rated LOW as they apply to teams already past basic ML deployment.
### Proposed Resolution: Add a "Feature Engineering and Data Versioning" section to mlops. Triggers: "feature store", "training data versioning", "data lineage". Scope: Cover DVC for dataset versioning, basic feature consistency checks between training and serving, and data validation schemas using Great Expectations or Pandera.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 4 eval_harness covers model evaluation but not data quality validation upstream of training. Phase 7 (Maintenance) has no pattern for investigating model degradation back to its training data source.

