## Finding: Phase 4 → Phase 5 Handoff: Test Results Don't Gate Deployment

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: Phase 4 (Secure) produces: unit test results, integration test results, E2E test results, security audit findings, performance test baselines, and accessibility reports. Phase 5 (ci_cd_pipeline) re-runs lint, type-check, and unit tests as PR checks. However: (1) there is no mechanism for Phase 5's deployment pipeline to consume Phase 4's test artifacts — if Phase 4's E2E or integration tests are in a separate pipeline, their pass/fail status does not gate Phase 5's production deploy; (2) the performance test baselines from Phase 4 are not carried into Phase 5 as regression thresholds; (3) the security_audit checklist from Phase 4 produces no machine-readable artifact that Phase 5's deployment gate can check. Phase 5 rediscovers everything from scratch in CI rather than building on Phase 4's validated state.
### Proposed Resolution: Define a "Phase 4 → Phase 5 handoff contract": a required artifact set that Phase 4 must produce before Phase 5 deployment is authorized. This could be a GitHub Actions reusable workflow that: (1) requires Phase 4's test suite workflow to have passed in the last N hours; (2) consumes performance baselines as environment variables; (3) checks that security_audit checklist items are marked complete. Document this in both phase skill sets.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Without this gate, Phase 5 effectively ignores the extensive work of Phase 4. A project could skip Phase 4 entirely and Phase 5 would still deploy. This undermines the entire phase-gate model of the framework.

