## Finding: Phase 5 → Phase 5.5 Handoff: Alpha Receives No "Deployment Manifest"

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Phase 5.5 (Alpha) skills (health_checks, env_validation, error_tracking, backup_strategy, qa_playbook) all assume they are being configured "after" Phase 5 deployment. However: (1) Phase 5 produces no documented "deployment manifest" — a record of what was deployed (image tag/SHA, migration version, environment variables set, services running, external dependencies configured); (2) Phase 5.5's health_checks need to know what endpoints exist — but there is no Phase 5 artifact listing them; (3) Phase 5.5's env_validation needs to know what env vars are required — but Phase 5 produces no env var inventory; (4) Phase 5.5's backup_strategy needs the database connection details and schema version — but Phase 5 produces no structured output for this. The downstream phase operates blind.
### Proposed Resolution: Phase 5 should produce a standardized "deployment manifest" JSON artifact after every production deploy. Contents: deployed SHA/tag, migration version applied, environment name, health endpoint URLs, required env var names (not values), timestamp, deployed-by identity. This manifest becomes the input to Phase 5.5's onboarding. Encode this in the ci_cd_pipeline's final deploy step.
### Cross-Phase Impact: All Phase 5.5 skills would benefit. This also feeds Phase 6 (Handoff) documentation and Phase 7 (Maintenance) runbooks.

