### Gap Type: FAILURE_MODE_UNCOVERED
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: The infrastructure_as_code skill covers Terraform state management with S3 + DynamoDB locking. However, it does not cover: (1) what happens when a Terraform state lock is stuck (previous run crashed, lock was never released); (2) how to safely force-unlock the state during an emergency; (3) the risk of running `terraform apply` concurrently from two CI runs (race condition on lock acquisition); (4) Terraform plan diffs in CI as a review step before apply (only `plan` is mentioned but no PR-comment-plan-diff automation); (5) state file corruption recovery; (6) handling Terraform provider version drift. In a production incident, a stuck Terraform lock can block all infrastructure changes for hours.
### Proposed Resolution: Add "Operational Concerns" section to infrastructure_as_code: (1) stuck lock detection and safe force-unlock procedure; (2) concurrency control in CI (only allow one Terraform apply at a time via GitHub Actions concurrency groups); (3) Terraform plan-as-PR-comment automation (Atlantis or tfcmt); (4) state backup procedure.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 7 (Maintenance) runbooks need Terraform operational procedures. Phase 5.5 has no connection to infrastructure state management.

